24/04/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- During a weekend visit to Tirana, NATO Assistant Secretary General for Defence Policy and Planning John Colston praised the progress achieved in military reforms. According to local press reports Monday (24 April), Colston met with Prime Minister Sali Berisha and Defence Minister Fatmir Mediu to discuss Albania's bid for NATO membership. He called for strengthening the fight against organised crime and corruption and confirmed that NATO would continue to support the country's defence reform process. Colston was in Tirana for the 11th conference of the Albanian Atlantic Association. (Albanian News - 24/04/06; Albanian President Web site - 23/04/06)
